cal authors: from Thucydides and Plato to Machiavelli and Hobbes. Carlo Altini presents us with a philosopher who escapes any attempt at classification, who lived constantly in exile between theory and practice, philosophy and politics, immanence and transcendence, and who considered philosophy the most important critical exercise of human reason, always "out of date" and always "out of place."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aPhilosopherszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPhilosophy, Americany20th century. 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aHistory : History. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion and Politics. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Philosophers.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849007640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438490076423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438490076/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles